# Git Workflow

- Keep commits focused on one logical change.
- Write clear commit messages that describe intent, not just file changes.
- Do not include unrelated refactors in the same commit as feature work.

# Local Verification

- Run lint before committing.
- Run relevant tests for the touched modules before creating a PR.
- If a change affects shared behavior, run broader checks at repo root.

# Pre-commit Behavior

- Respect Husky and lint-staged hooks.
- Ensure staged files are clean so pre-commit checks pass without retries.
- Avoid bypassing hooks except for explicit emergency scenarios.

# Pull Request Quality

- Keep PR scope reviewable and coherent.
- Include short testing notes covering what was verified.
- Resolve feedback by updating code and tests together where appropriate.
